1
00:00:01,033 --> 00:00:02,767
<i> You rejected all of
my suggestions for a DJ?</i>

2
00:00:02,767 --> 00:00:04,767
<i> - It's expensive!
- You want something cheap?</i>

3
00:00:04,767 --> 00:00:06,667
<i> Then you do it yourself
so it's free!</i>

4
00:00:06,667 --> 00:00:08,433
<i> You've been gone from there
for more than a year.</i>

5
00:00:08,433 --> 00:00:10,633
<i>Will they still recognize
Luna Almazan?</i>

6
00:00:10,633 --> 00:00:11,967
<i> They know Luna,</i>

7
00:00:11,967 --> 00:00:15,667
<i> but they don't know Solenn.
</i>[CHUCKLES]

8
00:00:15,667 --> 00:00:17,500
<i> I hope we're always like this.</i>

9
00:00:18,533 --> 00:00:20,133
<i> I want to visit my brother.</i>

10
00:00:20,133 --> 00:00:21,833
<i> Since his Papa Mike
passed away...</i>

11
00:00:21,833 --> 00:00:24,667
<i>I want to do something
nice for him, and this is it.</i>

12
00:00:24,667 --> 00:00:25,633
<i> "U" for...</i>

13
00:00:25,633 --> 00:00:26,733
<i> "Utusero!" (Bossy!)</i>

14
00:00:26,733 --> 00:00:27,567
<i> Sir!</i>

15
00:00:27,567 --> 00:00:29,833
<i> You gave me
so many orders!</i>

16
00:00:29,833 --> 00:00:31,833
<i> You really need to hire
an assistant.</i>

17
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,167
<i> Raphie, did you post it?</i>

18
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:37,633
<i>I posted the correct
time and place</i>

19
00:00:37,633 --> 00:00:39,067
<i> so that many people would see</i>

20
00:00:39,067 --> 00:00:40,733
<i>that you're looking
for an assistant.</i>

21
00:00:40,733 --> 00:00:43,933
<i>So why is it that until now
not one of them is here?</i>

22
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:45,633
<i> Where are they?!</i>

23
00:00:46,967 --> 00:00:48,067
[SARI] Universe!

24
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:50,933
Please make it happen!

25
00:00:50,933 --> 00:00:52,800
Universe, give this to me.

26
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:54,033
This is mine now, universe.

27
00:00:54,667 --> 00:00:56,100
Universe...

28
00:00:56,100 --> 00:00:57,633
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

29
00:00:58,533 --> 00:01:00,800
Good morning, y'all!

30
00:01:04,733 --> 00:01:05,900
- [CHUCKLES]
- [PHONE RINGING]

31
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:06,867
Oh!

32
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:08,633
- [PHONE CHIMES]
- Hello, Grandpa?

33
00:01:09,733 --> 00:01:11,233
Hello, Sari?

34
00:01:11,233 --> 00:01:12,500
Where are you now?

35
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:14,967
I'm already here.
I'm just waiting for the boat.

36
00:01:16,133 --> 00:01:17,200
Well of course, Grandpa!

37
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:19,833
Who else would
they pick but me?

38
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:22,500
Just me and no one else.

39
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:23,500
What?

40
00:01:23,867 --> 00:01:25,233
Someone else already got hired?

41
00:01:25,233 --> 00:01:26,400
Huh?!

42
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:28,767
They already hired someone
from Hotel 88?

43
00:01:30,067 --> 00:01:31,100
They hired someone else?

44
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:33,567
[WOMAN 1] Miss, did they hire
someone already?

45
00:01:33,967 --> 00:01:35,767
<i>Then why are we still
going there?</i>

46
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:38,033
Someone else already got hired?

47
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:40,067
- Let's just leave.
- Let's go.

48
00:01:40,067 --> 00:01:41,800
- Hello, Grandpa!
- Sari?

49
00:01:41,833 --> 00:01:43,233
- Grandpa, I can't understand.
- Who's the deaf one here?

50
00:01:43,233 --> 00:01:45,033
<i>- You or me?
- What are you saying, Grandpa?</i>

51
00:01:46,033 --> 00:01:50,567
<i> No, I'm asking you
</i>if someone else already got it.

52
00:01:50,567 --> 00:01:52,800
Universe, this is mine!

53
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:54,067
[CHUCKLES SLIGHTLY]

54
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:59,733
I'll just call you later, okay?

55
00:01:59,733 --> 00:02:01,000
- I'll update you.
- [MAN] Oh, Solara island!

56
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,033
- Solara island!
- Okay, Grandpa! Bye!

57
00:02:02,033 --> 00:02:03,733
Me! Me! Me!

58
00:02:03,733 --> 00:02:04,767
Where are the others?

59
00:02:05,233 --> 00:02:06,800
Oh, I don't know.

60
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:09,000
They suddenly left.
Maybe they got tired of waiting.

61
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,900
I thought they were going
to apply at Hotel 88?

62
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:12,200
That's what I thought too.

63
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:14,867
But it turns out
I'm the one and only

64
00:02:14,900 --> 00:02:17,167
future assistant of Hotel 88!
[CHUCKLES]

65
00:02:17,167 --> 00:02:18,667
- Let's go! Let's go!
- Let's go!

66
00:02:18,667 --> 00:02:25,633
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

67
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:39,633
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

68
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:35,700
[FOOTSTEPS]

69
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:45,767
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

70
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:48,367
Raphie.

71
00:03:49,067 --> 00:03:50,267
Are we expecting a guest?

72
00:03:50,267 --> 00:03:51,833
What's Martin doing there?

73
00:03:52,233 --> 00:03:54,133
[GIO] He's hiring
an executive assistant.

74
00:03:54,167 --> 00:03:59,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

75
00:03:59,367 --> 00:04:00,767
Assistant?

76
00:04:00,767 --> 00:04:02,800
I don't even have an assistant,
and he's getting one?

77
00:04:03,300 --> 00:04:05,000
Relax. Don't worry.

78
00:04:05,433 --> 00:04:07,133
He's the one paying the salary.

79
00:04:07,133 --> 00:04:09,733
It won't come out of the
hotel's magical budget.

80
00:04:09,733 --> 00:04:16,667
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

81
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:18,767
[CUP CLINKS]

82
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:22,900
[SIGHS]

83
00:04:33,167 --> 00:04:34,467
[GIO] Cup noodles?

84
00:04:34,467 --> 00:04:41,400
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

85
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:42,933
[CUP CLINKS]

86
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:45,767
[CUP NOODLES CLINKS]

87
00:04:46,967 --> 00:04:47,933
[SIGHS]

88
00:04:55,133 --> 00:04:56,233
[CHUCKLES SLIGHTLY]

89
00:04:57,367 --> 00:05:04,300
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

90
00:05:06,767 --> 00:05:07,933
Bro, uh...

91
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:08,933
Do you have
any recommendations

92
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:09,933
for an assistant?

93
00:05:09,933 --> 00:05:11,300
I would greatly appreciate it.

94
00:05:13,133 --> 00:05:14,833
If I don't find anyone here,

95
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:16,467
maybe you might know
someone.

96
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:21,867
Goodness! Sir really can't wait.

97
00:05:24,967 --> 00:05:27,000
[BOAT ENGINE HUMMING]

98
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:30,300
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

99
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:32,167
Uh, are they here?

100
00:05:32,167 --> 00:05:35,333
[STAMMERS] T-There!
There they are! Sir! Sir Martin!

101
00:05:35,367 --> 00:05:37,367
Sir Martin, they're here!

102
00:05:37,367 --> 00:05:39,833
They're here! They're here!

103
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:46,767
- [BOAT ENGINE HUMMING]
- [SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

104
00:05:51,033 --> 00:05:52,167
Just one?

105
00:06:01,267 --> 00:06:08,200
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

106
00:06:23,067 --> 00:06:25,500
[SARI] Ma! Pa!

107
00:06:26,433 --> 00:06:29,267
<i> I've been waiting for so long.</i>

108
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:32,300
<i> How long will I be alone?</i>

109
00:06:33,167 --> 00:06:36,767
<i> Grandpa said I would meet
my soulmate.</i>

110
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:40,267
<i>Because one day,
the sky will cry...</i>

111
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,833
<i>...and its tears
will fall to the ground.</i>

112
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:46,267
<i>- But when will that happen?
- [THUNDER RUMBLING]</i>

113
00:06:46,267 --> 00:06:53,267
- [THUNDER RUMBLING]
- [RAIN POURING]

114
00:06:53,267 --> 00:07:00,200
["SILONG KA MUNA"
BY BRYAN CHONG PLAYING]

115
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:12,067
[SARI]<i> Back then, I asked
</i> the universe for signs

116
00:07:12,067 --> 00:07:14,333
<i>that I would meet
my soulmate...</i>

117
00:07:16,433 --> 00:07:17,900
<i> That one day...</i>

118
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:19,333
<i> the sky would cry</i>

119
00:07:19,333 --> 00:07:22,367
<i>and its tears would fall
to the ground.</i>

120
00:07:25,467 --> 00:07:32,400
["SILONG KA MUNA" CONTINUES]

121
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,133
<i> They say...</i>

122
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:50,033
just because you want something
<i> doesn't mean you'll get it.</i>

123
00:07:50,067 --> 00:07:51,400
<i> But I say,</i>

124
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:52,967
<i> if it's truly meant for me,</i>

125
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:55,333
<i> then it's something
worth fighting for, sis!</i>

126
00:07:58,267 --> 00:08:05,200
["SILONG KA MUNA" CONTINUES]

127
00:08:11,267 --> 00:08:13,867
<i> You're so good, universe!</i>

128
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,100
Just you?

129
00:08:19,667 --> 00:08:21,000
Yes, sir.

130
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,100
Just me.

131
00:08:22,567 --> 00:08:25,133
All yours, completely.

132
00:08:25,133 --> 00:08:32,067
["SILONG KA MUNA" CONTINUES]

133
00:08:38,467 --> 00:08:40,367
I need someone
who's good with scheduling.

134
00:08:40,367 --> 00:08:42,200
I'm the class secretary
since fifth grade.

135
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:45,600
I even record the boatman's
schedule as a hobby.

136
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,667
Can you work under pressure?

137
00:08:46,667 --> 00:08:48,867
Sir, even if you put me
in a pressure cooker,

138
00:08:48,867 --> 00:08:51,467
I'll never be soft nor weak.

139
00:08:52,367 --> 00:08:54,800
I don't want an employee
who chooses her tasks.

140
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:56,600
I'll shine your shoes,

141
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:58,633
I'll make you fried water,

142
00:08:58,633 --> 00:09:01,900
and even if you make me count
all the tiles in this hotel,

143
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:03,633
I won't complain.

144
00:09:06,367 --> 00:09:07,400
Sir?

145
00:09:07,633 --> 00:09:08,867
Flower?

146
00:09:09,467 --> 00:09:11,667
Or would you like a heart?
I can do that, too.

147
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:15,600
Am I hired?

148
00:09:16,867 --> 00:09:19,867
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYS]

149
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:24,333
[XANDER]
Alright, pose. Nice one.

150
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,767
Okay, one more.

151
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:28,333
- Alright.
- [CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

152
00:09:28,967 --> 00:09:30,233
Now, move closer.

153
00:09:30,433 --> 00:09:31,667
Alright.

154
00:09:32,467 --> 00:09:34,867
After this, let's do
a photoshoot in the rooms.

155
00:09:35,467 --> 00:09:37,600
Aren't we going to the beach?

156
00:09:37,933 --> 00:09:39,533
I was looking forward to it.

157
00:09:40,267 --> 00:09:42,233
So, do I just have to wear
a bathrobe now?

158
00:09:42,700 --> 00:09:43,867
Bathrobe?

159
00:09:45,667 --> 00:09:48,333
Come on, Jade.
I need to see the beach.

160
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:50,800
It's part of my promotion
for Hotel 88.

161
00:09:51,933 --> 00:09:53,333
[SIGHS]

162
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:56,967
Okay, fine. Fine.

163
00:09:56,967 --> 00:09:59,733
Let's go to the beach
after this, okay?

164
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:04,767
[LIGHTHEARTED MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:13,033
Excuse me.

166
00:10:14,767 --> 00:10:18,767
["PANGHABANG IKAW"
BY DARREN PLAYING]

167
00:10:41,667 --> 00:10:43,500
[WATER SPLASHES]

168
00:10:49,567 --> 00:10:53,100
Mister Xander,
can we go over here by the pool?

169
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:55,100
[STAMMERING] Let's take photos.

170
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:57,767
Take many photos.
One wide shot, and...

171
00:10:57,767 --> 00:11:00,100
[JADE] Yeah, that's good.

172
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:02,367
And hurry up,
we're going to the beach next.

173
00:11:02,367 --> 00:11:05,800
Also, take a close-up shot.
A bit closer...

174
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:08,633
Yeah, that's perfect.
That's perfect.

175
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:10,967
[JADE] Excuse me,
you're kind of in the frame.

176
00:11:10,967 --> 00:11:13,500
C-Can you move a bit?

177
00:11:13,733 --> 00:11:16,367
A bit-- Alright. Sorry,
we're just doing promos.

178
00:11:16,367 --> 00:11:17,967
Keep clicking, go on.

179
00:11:17,967 --> 00:11:20,567
Can you up the brightness
a bit, too?

180
00:11:20,567 --> 00:11:22,000
Okay. Thank you.

181
00:11:28,467 --> 00:11:29,700
Remember, okay?

182
00:11:29,700 --> 00:11:31,433
Don't take a bath
for three weeks.

183
00:11:31,433 --> 00:11:32,667
- A sponge bath will do.
- Yes, sir.

184
00:11:32,667 --> 00:11:34,500
- Go on now.
- Thank you.

185
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:35,500
- Thank you, sir.
- Alright.

186
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:37,400
Grandpa! Grandpa!

187
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:38,900
Grandpa!

188
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,967
Grandpa! Grandpa!

189
00:11:42,433 --> 00:11:43,700
- Oh?
- Oh...

190
00:11:44,867 --> 00:11:46,000
Blessings, Grandpa.

191
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,733
- What is it?
- It's a success!

192
00:11:47,733 --> 00:11:49,533
- What?
- A success, Grandpa!

193
00:11:49,533 --> 00:11:50,533
- Grandpa!
- Yes?

194
00:11:50,533 --> 00:11:52,500
I just got hired at Hotel 88!

195
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:54,700
What?! You got fired?

196
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:56,400
- Now, why did you--
- No, Grandpa!

197
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:57,900
Hired! I got hired!

198
00:11:57,900 --> 00:11:59,867
- H-hired?
- I got hired!

199
00:11:59,867 --> 00:12:01,400
At the Hotel 88?

200
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:04,633
[BOTH CHEERING]

201
00:12:06,433 --> 00:12:09,633
Who wouldn't want you
as their employee?

202
00:12:09,633 --> 00:12:11,400
No one, of course!

203
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,100
- But, Grandpa...
- Oh?

204
00:12:13,633 --> 00:12:15,833
The boss is so handsome!

205
00:12:16,100 --> 00:12:18,133
He cheeks are so rosy,

206
00:12:18,533 --> 00:12:20,567
I want to bite into them!

207
00:12:20,567 --> 00:12:22,967
Hey, Sari! That's bad.

208
00:12:22,967 --> 00:12:24,033
Uh... [CHUCKLES]

209
00:12:24,033 --> 00:12:25,167
- I'm just kidding.
- Mm?

210
00:12:25,167 --> 00:12:26,667
I'm probably just hungry.

211
00:12:26,667 --> 00:12:28,433
That's why I want
to bite into something.

212
00:12:28,433 --> 00:12:29,467
Hmm?

213
00:12:29,467 --> 00:12:30,867
- But, Grandpa...
- What?

214
00:12:30,867 --> 00:12:32,400
- You know...
- What's this?

215
00:12:32,867 --> 00:12:36,933
Tell me what the future holds
for me and Sir Martin!

216
00:12:36,933 --> 00:12:38,033
Not right now!

217
00:12:38,667 --> 00:12:39,767
Yes, why not?

218
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:41,700
- Starting tomorrow...
- Mm.

219
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:42,767
[SIGHS]

220
00:12:42,767 --> 00:12:45,633
Tomorrow will be my first day

221
00:12:45,633 --> 00:12:47,733
as an executive assistant

222
00:12:47,967 --> 00:12:49,800
at Hotel 88.

223
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:50,967
[SQUEALS]

224
00:12:50,967 --> 00:12:53,600
[BOTH CHEER]

225
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:54,633
Grandpa!

226
00:12:54,867 --> 00:12:57,867
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

227
00:13:12,233 --> 00:13:15,433
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

228
00:13:25,233 --> 00:13:27,200
[MUSIC TURNS SINISTER]

229
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:30,967
[GRUNTS, GROANS]

230
00:13:32,133 --> 00:13:34,567
[GROANING, CHOKES]

231
00:13:39,967 --> 00:13:42,267
[GRUNTS, GROANS]

232
00:13:43,133 --> 00:13:45,300
[GROANING, CHOKES]

233
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:53,500
[GRUNTING]

234
00:13:58,433 --> 00:13:59,533
[GROANS]

235
00:14:00,533 --> 00:14:02,500
[PANTING]

236
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,067
[BLOWS LAND]

237
00:14:14,433 --> 00:14:16,167
[GROANS]

238
00:14:19,267 --> 00:14:22,333
[BLOWS LAND]

239
00:14:23,633 --> 00:14:24,967
[KICK LANDS]

240
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:30,367
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

241
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:48,300
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

242
00:15:05,267 --> 00:15:08,367
Diana, don't forget
about tomorrow.

243
00:15:08,367 --> 00:15:10,567
Get all the things I ordered

244
00:15:10,567 --> 00:15:12,600
from the Italian restaurant
in town.

245
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:15,433
It's for Justin's birthday
tomorrow.

246
00:15:16,133 --> 00:15:17,100
Thank you.

247
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,000
Jade.

248
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:23,067
Should I make you some dinner?

249
00:15:24,667 --> 00:15:26,033
I'm still full.

250
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:28,267
Then maybe you can help me.

251
00:15:29,167 --> 00:15:31,067
It's Justin's birthday tomorrow.

252
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:33,633
Can you help me plan
a surprise for him?

253
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:36,600
I'll do it if that's
what you want to hear.

254
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:39,433
Jade...

255
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:41,700
I'm gonna take a rest, Mom.

256
00:15:42,433 --> 00:15:43,433
Jade...

257
00:15:44,533 --> 00:15:46,633
I've told you the truth.

258
00:15:47,167 --> 00:15:49,367
I hope you believe me.

259
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:51,600
[SIGHS]

260
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:55,300
What I believe right now,

261
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:58,933
is that you want
to be out of our lives.

262
00:16:02,067 --> 00:16:03,200
Good night, Mom.

263
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:06,633
Jade...

264
00:16:09,067 --> 00:16:12,033
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYS]

265
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:16,733
[PANTING]

266
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:20,600
[GROANING IN PAIN]

267
00:16:24,533 --> 00:16:27,267
[PANTING]

268
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:35,467
[GROANS]

269
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:42,667
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

270
00:16:43,667 --> 00:16:46,800
Who knew my clients
could actually be useful?

271
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:48,667
They're all increasing
the likes on the post.

272
00:16:49,933 --> 00:16:51,000
[PHONE DINGS]

273
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:58,367
- [SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

274
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:10,467
[SCOFFS]

275
00:17:10,467 --> 00:17:13,833
Well, look at that, it looks
like Gio's earning money.

276
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:15,933
We're finally getting our money.

277
00:17:15,967 --> 00:17:18,600
Good thing we pulled
a fast one on Gio.

278
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:21,567
That item you made him sell
was so easy to steal.

279
00:17:21,567 --> 00:17:24,633
Once he pays me 400,000,

280
00:17:24,633 --> 00:17:27,467
we'll keep milking Gio
for more money.

281
00:17:27,467 --> 00:17:32,033
- [LAUGHTER]
- This fool is so easy to scam.

282
00:17:33,533 --> 00:17:37,033
A lot of people are interested
in our hotel.

283
00:17:37,033 --> 00:17:39,367
Martin mentioned that...

284
00:17:39,367 --> 00:17:41,467
a lot of people are booking us.

285
00:17:41,467 --> 00:17:43,900
That's because
of Edward's efforts.

286
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:46,433
He made one post...

287
00:17:46,433 --> 00:17:47,867
and the feedback was great.

288
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,800
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

289
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:52,367
People are also booking
for the music fest.

290
00:17:53,567 --> 00:17:56,500
It's thanks to Edward that we're
getting all these reservations.

291
00:17:56,500 --> 00:18:01,033
[ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

292
00:18:01,033 --> 00:18:02,767
Gio, what are you doing?

293
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:06,333
Gio...

294
00:18:07,033 --> 00:18:09,433
Tell me the truth.

295
00:18:09,433 --> 00:18:11,367
You still have feelings
for me, don't you?

296
00:18:12,733 --> 00:18:14,667
You're pretty shameless,
aren't you?

297
00:18:16,900 --> 00:18:18,667
You're being
so snappy with me.

298
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:22,967
If you really don't have
any feelings...

299
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,467
you should be indifferent.

300
00:18:25,467 --> 00:18:27,100
You're overthinking this again.

301
00:18:29,033 --> 00:18:31,433
Do you want to know
what I'm thinking of?

302
00:18:31,433 --> 00:18:38,367
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

303
00:18:42,967 --> 00:18:44,833
If you have
nothing more to say...

304
00:18:46,567 --> 00:18:47,800
What?

305
00:18:49,967 --> 00:18:51,900
Are you going
to kick me out again?

306
00:18:56,967 --> 00:18:58,700
You're not really
over me yet.

307
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:04,700
Is this what
you're talking about?

308
00:19:08,133 --> 00:19:09,567
I can do it.

309
00:19:12,967 --> 00:19:14,467
Can you?

310
00:19:14,467 --> 00:19:21,400
[ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

311
00:19:30,067 --> 00:19:33,767
You just dropped by, right?
You're not working today.

312
00:19:35,033 --> 00:19:38,633
- Go ahead.
- Okay.

313
00:19:42,900 --> 00:19:45,833
[MARTIN] This house
is off limits to the guests.

314
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:47,800
My brothers
and I lived here.

315
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:50,500
How about me, sir?
Can I stay here too?

316
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:53,167
Only if I'm there,
Understood?

317
00:19:53,167 --> 00:19:57,133
Copy. Noted. Got it.
I can handle it. [GIGGLES]

318
00:19:57,133 --> 00:19:58,933
[SIGHS] We'll go up
to the hotel.

319
00:19:58,933 --> 00:20:03,200
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

320
00:20:03,233 --> 00:20:06,033
I'm in charge today because
the GM isn't there right now.

321
00:20:06,033 --> 00:20:07,833
Actually, all the Almazans.

322
00:20:07,833 --> 00:20:10,967
Call the supplier of toiletries,
we need more stocks.

323
00:20:10,967 --> 00:20:14,533
Then call the technician,
we need the rooms checked.

324
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:19,100
- Are you listing this?
- Yes, sir.

325
00:20:19,100 --> 00:20:21,667
Here, and in here.

326
00:20:21,667 --> 00:20:24,133
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

327
00:20:24,133 --> 00:20:25,733
[GROANS]

328
00:20:32,067 --> 00:20:34,100
Is that it? This is it!

329
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:38,667
It's beautiful! I've only
seen this in pictures.

330
00:20:38,667 --> 00:20:40,667
It's beautiful!

331
00:20:40,667 --> 00:20:42,767
It's beautiful!
Look-- Oh! I'm sorry!

332
00:20:42,767 --> 00:20:45,033
- Excuse me.
- I'm sorry, I didn't mean to.

333
00:20:45,033 --> 00:20:46,967
Hey, I'm sorry!

334
00:20:46,967 --> 00:20:50,833
[SCOFFS] Her head is hotter than
the sun here on the island.

335
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:58,700
[MAN] Island Solara?
Right here!

336
00:20:59,767 --> 00:21:02,933
- Let me carry those, ma'am.
- Are you going to Hotel 88?

337
00:21:02,933 --> 00:21:05,667
- Yes.
- Are you a guest there?

338
00:21:05,667 --> 00:21:07,833
Obviously. And you?

339
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:09,700
I'm a guest there too!

340
00:21:12,033 --> 00:21:15,267
There is no CCTV
in the area you mentioned.

341
00:21:15,267 --> 00:21:16,467
I knew it.

342
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:20,133
Have the other CCTVs
in that town checked.

343
00:21:20,133 --> 00:21:24,500
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

344
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:27,333
Are you really sure that...

345
00:21:27,333 --> 00:21:29,033
you didn't see
that person's face?

346
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:33,433
Just to be sure.

347
00:21:36,533 --> 00:21:39,967
It's been a long time since
someone attacked me like that.

348
00:21:39,967 --> 00:21:43,433
It started when I drabbled with
the Almazan and Fernandez case.

349
00:21:45,900 --> 00:21:47,500
Which one of them do
you suspect?

350
00:21:49,067 --> 00:21:50,867
[HENRI] I don't know.

351
00:21:50,867 --> 00:21:53,333
But I'm sure someone
wants to keep me quiet.

352
00:21:54,367 --> 00:21:57,333
So I don't have to look
into that case.

353
00:21:57,333 --> 00:21:59,433
This case
isn't over yet, Marina.

354
00:22:00,467 --> 00:22:04,133
I need to know more about
Michael and Federico's deaths.

355
00:22:05,967 --> 00:22:06,933
[HENRI EXHALES]

356
00:22:06,933 --> 00:22:11,600
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

357
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:14,267
When you get to Mr. Felipe
tell him to get

358
00:22:14,267 --> 00:22:17,900
my usual order cheese
and cold cuts.

359
00:22:17,933 --> 00:22:21,400
Tell him to add more
salted pork belly, alright?

360
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:23,567
Remember my instructions.

361
00:22:27,633 --> 00:22:33,967
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

362
00:22:33,967 --> 00:22:35,600
I've done what
you told me to do, ma'am.

363
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:40,267
[MUSIC SWELLS]

364
00:22:40,267 --> 00:22:41,533
Are you sure?

365
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:44,867
Yes, ma'am.

366
00:22:47,967 --> 00:22:49,633
Alright. Thank you.

367
00:22:49,667 --> 00:22:56,633
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

368
00:23:02,533 --> 00:23:05,567
<i>Give me the VIP room!
The most expensive one!</i>

369
00:23:05,567 --> 00:23:07,567
<i>- This is the VIP, right?
- Uh, yes.</i>

370
00:23:07,567 --> 00:23:10,200
<i> We can't just avoid
each other all the time!</i>

371
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:11,933
<i> Do you want to know the truth?</i>

372
00:23:11,933 --> 00:23:14,400
<i>If you weren't my sister,
I would've punched you</i>

373
00:23:14,400 --> 00:23:15,633
<i> because of how wrong
your timing is!</i>

374
00:23:15,633 --> 00:23:18,100
- [SQUEALS]<i> Hi, sissy!
</i>- [GASPS] Oh.

375
00:23:18,100 --> 00:23:20,900
<i>- She's my assistant.
- Ah... assistant.</i>

376
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:23,900
<i>- Surprise!
- Aren't they mourning?</i>

377
00:23:23,933 --> 00:23:27,000
Aunt Frida wasn't there when we
went to the crime scene, right?

378
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:29,467
<i>Could she have something
to do with their deaths?</i>

379
00:23:29,467 --> 00:23:32,367
<i>Mrs. Almazan, where were you
when Michael Fernandez</i>

380
00:23:32,367 --> 00:23:34,033
<i> and Federico Almazan died?</i>

